             <h3 style="text-align:center; color:#F25C27;">Smart Materials and Sensory Devices</h3>
            <p class="ser">Smart Materials, a significant solution for the 21st century’s technological needs, are materials that are capable of sensing and actively responding to the environment by changing their physical properties, such as shape, size and colour. There are many groups of smart materials, each exhibiting particular properties which can be harnessed in a variety of high-tech and everyday applications. <br>
The workshop “Smart Materials and Sensory Devices” facilitates to share current research experiences of eminent scientists with budding engineers in grounds of Shape Memory Alloys, Micro Electro Mechanical Systems, Piezoelectric materials and Magnetic nano fluid sensors. We take pride in inviting you to the one-day extravaganza.</p>
