                  <h4>Shape Memory Alloys</h4>
                  <p class="sg">The SME describes the process of a material changing shape or remembering a particular shape at a specific temperature (i.e. its transformation or memory temperature).At the memory temperature the alloy undergoes a solid state phase transformation. Within few years, SMAs will be used as artificial muscles, i.e. simulating the expansion and contraction of human muscles. This process will utilise a piece of SMA wire in place of a muscle on the finger of a robotic hand.</p>
             </div>

             <div class="col-md-3 service-grid workshop-grid wow fadeInLeft animated" data-wow-delay="0.4s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.4s; animation-name: fadeInLeft;">           
